Questions:
Which of the following procedures in the study is considered experimental for the treatment of prostate cancer patients with evidence of homologous recombination deficiency?
A) Standard hormonal therapies for prostate cancer;
B) Administration of olaparib twice daily to study its clinical effects;
C) Routine CT scans and bone scans to monitor the progression of the disease;
D) Use of condoms and other contraceptive methods during the study period.

Correct answer: B) Administration of olaparib twice daily to study its clinical effects.

Who is responsible for ensuring the confidentiality of your personal health information if you participate in the Olaparib prostate cancer study?
A) The study sponsor, AstraZeneca, and their agents;
B) Institutional Review Boards (IRBs), including the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center IRB;
C) Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center, University of Washington;
D) All of the above

Correct answer: D
